📍@kalayaphilly 

jui guay - steamed rice cups with shiitake mushrooms, bamboo shoots and spicy sweet soy sauce

gui chai - crispy garlic chive rice cakes with spicy sweet soy sauce

prik king jae - wok-cooked dry red curry with crispy tofu, long beans and long hot peppers, served with jasmine rice

durian sticky rice 

By @resy reservation notification, we scored a 6 pm Monday spot on Sunday afternoon.  I would recommend everything.  The spice and service levels were HIGH and I cannot wait to go back.

This weekend 🥰 @monsterveganphilly — first off, the Argento is one of our favorite sandwiches in the city. Some of our other favs are the General Tso’s Wings, Fried Mac & Cheese Balls and Truffle Fries (the horseradish aioli is 💣). We also tried a new to us item, the Panzarotti, it was phenomenal and comes with the house ala vodka sauce which is unreal.
The only redeeming quality of jury duty is this @luhvfood Caprese which was 10/10 🍅🥖

✈️ Day 1: Amsterdam

We wandered all around this beautiful city today and had two major food stops — @margosamsterdam & @veganjunkfoodbar. I have been eyeing up both of these place for a while so it was exciting. 

At Margo’s, we tried the Ham & Cheese Croissant, Apricot Danish and Lemon Lavender Danish.  All three options were unreal and we are fighting the urge to go there everyday. 

At Vegan Junk Food Bar, we ordered the Nachos 😍, Sumo Platter (basically an appetizer sampler) and Triple Trouble (slider sampler essentially). It was delicious and just what we needed.
Vegan rijsttafel at Mama Makan in Amsterdam 😍
Celebrated 6 years at @primary_plant_based last night 🖤 Everything was fantastic, as always.
